author: Hans Egli, 2002, Paiwanwörterbuch. Harrassowitz
notes: This dictionary is generally ignored in the Formosan literature because it is in German. The orthography has been converted to that of Ferrell's Paiwan dictionary, in order to facilitate comparison.
problems: Egli cites most verbs in their actor voice form, with m(V)- or -em-. Forms in  m(V)-  are segmented by a hyphen. I have omitted the -em- infix from list items, as it is predictable.
